        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 11:38PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1138 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Demopolis, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
U.S. 80 and AL 28, Newbern, Greensboro Municipal Airport, Jefferson,
Demopolis, Old Spring Hill, Belmont, Pin Hook, Selden Lock And Dam,
Forkland, Demopolis Lock And Dam, Gallion, Walden Quarters, McDowell,
Duffys Bend, Sawyerville, Arcola, Birdine, Laneville, and Cedarville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
